            <td class="align-top">bytes<wbr>Scanned<wbr>Cutoff<wbr>Per<wbr>Query</td>
            <td class="align-top"><code>number</code></td>
            <td class="align-top">{{% md %}}
(Optional) Integer for the upper data usage limit (cutoff) for the amount of bytes a single query in a workgroup is allowed to scan. Must be at least `10485760`.

{{% /md %}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td class="align-top">enforce<wbr>Workgroup<wbr>Configuration</td>
            <td class="align-top"><code>boolean</code></td>
            <td class="align-top">{{% md %}}
(Optional) Boolean whether the settings for the workgroup override client-side settings. For more information, see [Workgroup Settings Override Client-Side Settings](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/athena/latest/ug/workgroups-settings-override.html). Defaults to `true`.

{{% /md %}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td class="align-top">publish<wbr>Cloudwatch<wbr>Metrics<wbr>Enabled</td>
            <td class="align-top"><code>boolean</code></td>
            <td class="align-top">{{% md %}}
(Optional) Boolean whether Amazon CloudWatch metrics are enabled for the workgroup. Defaults to `true`.

{{% /md %}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td class="align-top">result<wbr>Configuration</td>

#### WorkgroupConfigurationResultConfigurationEncryptionConfiguration

<table class="ml-6">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Argument</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Description</th>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td class="align-top">encryption<wbr>Option</td>
            <td class="align-top"><code>string</code></td>
            <td class="align-top">{{% md %}}
(Optional) Indicates whether Amazon S3 server-side encryption with Amazon S3-managed keys (SSE-S3), server-side encryption with KMS-managed keys (SSE-KMS), or client-side encryption with KMS-managed keys (CSE-KMS) is used. If a query runs in a workgroup and the workgroup overrides client-side settings, then the workgroup's setting for encryption is used. It specifies whether query results must be encrypted, for all queries that run in this workgroup.

{{% /md %}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td class="align-top">kms<wbr>Key<wbr>Arn</td>
            <td class="align-top"><code>string</code></td>
            <td class="align-top">{{% md %}}
(Optional) For SSE-KMS and CSE-KMS, this is the KMS key Amazon Resource Name (ARN).

{{% /md %}}</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
